Battery backed SRAM ??<br />Not only normal NES boards doesn't have a slot for battery, but also all games that want to write to the mapper will ERASE rom data.<br />It would only go for board with bus conflicts, and those doesn't have battery.<br /><br />Also, I cannot find any existing EEPROM above the 28C256 (32kbx8).<br />Flashrom has different pinout so a lot of rewiring is needed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Mon Oct 02, 2006 11:14 am</p><hr />
